# CODEOWNERS — the architect owns review of every change (principle 3, ADR-0004).
#
# This is one of the THREE enforcement layers behind "agents propose, humans merge":
#   1. CODEOWNERS (this file) — a required reviewer on every PR
#   2. branch protection on the default branch — required review + status checks
#   3. a GitHub credential scoped WITHOUT merge rights (the maestro runtime token)
# See docs/guides/repo-controls.md for how to apply layers 2 and 3.
#
# Replace @fgurbanov with a GitHub team (e.g. @fps4/architects) if review should fan out.

# Everything requires architect review by default.
*                               @fgurbanov

# Governance-critical areas — called out so they can never silently lose an owner.
/docs/architecture/decisions/   @fgurbanov   # ADRs: immutable once accepted (ADR-0006)
/standards/                     @fgurbanov   # machine-injected SDLC floors (principle 9)
/config/                        @fgurbanov   # routing matrix + register (ADR-0003 / ADR-0008)
/.github/                       @fgurbanov   # the enforcement layer itself
